caption: It's not dine in
This place gives superb service as well as delicious menu. My favourite restaurant ever. The meals came out quickly and the rates are fair. Recommended.
The customer service is consistently speedy, excellent mood, super nice employees. Will return here again when I am in the area.

Next to the monument in Mt Vernon, this restaurant serves takeout food through Covid. I like the drunken noodles and my partner likes the curry.  Small team clearly putting a lot of work into this place - thanks!
I absolutely enjoyed the food and service, fantastic location next to my apartment. The workers are always welcoming. Will come visit again.
On a very very short list of my favorite Thai restaurants in Baltimore! Fantastic Ba Me Duck—highly recommended.
Suuuuuper slow, at least on my visit. "20 minutes" for takeaway turned into an hour.

My favorite Thai food in Baltimore. Try the Prik King Chicken. I appreciate that they're taking precautions during the pandemic and only offering well-spaced outdoor seating, along with delivery and takeout.

The food here is phenomenal. I lived in Thailand for 6 months and this really brought me back. The papaya salad was exactly like I remember and the ingredients for both my orders were delicious and fresh. I'll definitely be back to get more.
This place is great and broad, the menu was delicious and the rates were very affordable. rapidly, effective service and very friendly staff members. I highly recommend this place.

Called at 7:50 to place an order. They didn’t answer. By the time they finally picked up at 7:55 they told me they wouldn’t take my order because they close at 8. This is after they messed my order up previously

Recently went to Kuhn Nine with my boyfriend after our kitchen sink was clogged for about a week. On a Thursday night we were pretty surprised that there was nobody there but we sat down and ordered nonetheless. As lovers of Thai food we were very impressed. The service was very quick, food was clearly made to order as it was scaldingly hot when we received it. A couple weeks later, we visited again with family and though the restaurant was more crowded, the service was just as quick. Nice atmosphere as well, but you might miss it walking by, as it is wedged between two other restaurants. Absolutely worth a try!
Small portions and mediocre food, walk the extra 2 blocks and check out Thai Landing.
Great food. A hidden gem.
Fast

Lovely little place.  The service was attentive and congenial.  And the food was simply delectable.  We enjoyed green papaya salad, green chicken curry, and ba me duck.  Loved it all, and the duck was an epiphany - crispy but light.  A new family favorite.  We shall return!
The BLACK sticky pumpkin rice dessert was nothing more that WHITE sticky rice with pumpkin. Although, even though it was WHITE sticky rice instead of BLACK sticky rice it was still DELICIOUS!
Food is average. It's a small place. Nothing great to describe. I feel taste of the food is pretty average.
What can I say?  You literally cannot go wrong.  Order anything and it will be amazing.
Very cozy, romantic Thai place. Yummy food, friendly staff, and warm atmosphere.
One of my favorite Thai spots. Everything I have tried is delicious and portioned just right. Always leave satisfied and full but not overfed.
Delicious. I'll be back soon

The place is very very small so either come early or order pick up, and the foods that were spicy were also sweet. They blended the spices and sweetness qiute well, but me amd my dad wanted spicy so we didn't really like it.
Khao soi on point!

One of my favorite new Thai places popping up around the city. Super authentic, like they barely speak English authentic, and they dont hold back on the spice. Small space with very limited outdoor seating. It has kind of a cozy kitchen vibe. Almost like you are eating in someone's dinning room. They do carryout and I'm pretty sure they are on at least one of the delivery apps.Follow @slplanning on Instagram for more foodie finds, things to do, freebies, pics, and videos.

Very cozy place for a nice Thai meal. Service is fast and quality of food is good. Dark setting but nice for a simple date or just chatting over a nice meal. Slightly on the pricey side for a student.
Charming eatery.  Loved the spring rolls!  Excellent service also.
Very cozy!

In Baltimore on business, walking from inner harbor to Penn station, and voila, a minimilist Thai place right on Charles Street... The Pad Key Mao was flavorful, spicey, basically spot on... I eat a lot of Thai food and would return withOUT hesitation.

Super yummy. My friend and I shared the duck noodle soup and basil seafood rice. The rice was Surprisingly spicy in a gentle way and the soup had a strong five spice flavor with a generous portion of duck. Ambiance was a bit mediocre but the food tasty.
Delicious!
Great food and service!
Best Thai food in Mount Vernon. Very small restaurant, probably only 4/5 tables.  No alcohol, but you can go right across the street and grab a bottle of wine and bring back to the restaurant.

An energetic place, this tiny restaurant is like the little engine that could. With room for only about a half dozen very close tables and an aisle, they spill out with a few sidewalk tables. The full seats and seemingly never ending carryout line attest to the great food. As vegetarians, we were pleased with the variety of entree options, and omnivores have an expansive range. Very reasonable prices. Don't drink too much, as if you need a restroom you will be directed to the restaurant next door. The slow though pleasant service (the second waitstaff had called out, we were told) and loud atmosphere brought the rating down from a 5 to a 4. I still recommend it!
The food is amazing and the fact that you can bring your own bottle is a great plus

Very friendly service and I really enjoyed the food here! I had the red beef curry and it was the perfect spice level. I also tried my sister's pad kee mao and it was delicious. The mango sticky rice which I had for dessert was the standout at the end - if you go here it is a MUST TRY!!

I've ordered food for take out twice now. Both times, they told me it would be a 30 minute wait. It actually took over an hour. The first time they offered nothing for the 30 minutes I stood there waiting. The second time, they added an order of sticky rice to the menu. The food is fine, but I find the experience of attempting to get it so irritating, I couldn't enjoy it. I won't try again.
Good food, reasonably priced, efficiently served.  A no-frills place.
Absolutely Delicious! The pad-Thai here is second only to one I had in Thailand.
Really friendly environment and good food. Quick service with a well rounded menu
Great little spot for Thai. No selection of heat, just comes out 1 level - super tasty! Enjoyed the spring rolls and pad key mao.

Phoned in to place an order; they picked up and ignored any and all attempts to start an order. Sounded like the person decided to just place the phone on the counter and just let us hear the background drone of a kitchen conversation. Upon phoning back we were told that the voicemail was full. Incredible 10/10
No bathroom, busy so somewhat slow service, but food was fantastic

Ordered on Postmates but the delivery time kept being pushed back. After one hour, we called the restaurant multiple times, no one answered. Then we got a call from the Postmates driver that this restaurant did not cook our food yet. Very unprofessional and horrible service.
Good service with tasty food
The service is really bed .. the servers don’t speak English as well .. they are not training well... I don’t recommend this place ..!
Small space good food

Absolutely love this Thai place. It is the definition of “hole in the wall” however the food is fantastic and they service is generally done quickly. On a nice day, it is a wonderful place to sit outside and enjoy their drunken noodle.

I really wanted to like this place, but I have never dealt with such unapologetically rude and unprofessional customer service. It's such a shame because the food is actually good.  A friend from out-of-town was visiting me on 2/14/19 and wanted to order an early dinner from Khun Nine Thai. Realizing that it might be crowded on Valentine's Day, I called the restaurant at 5:55pm, but it went straight to voicemail. Instead, we decided to place an order for pickup through Grub Hub. The app immediately confirmed my order at 6:08pm and claimed that the restaurant began preparing my food at 6:10pm and that the pickup ETA was between 6:30-6:40pm. After placing my order, I received a call from the restaurant at 6:11pm to let us know that our order would actually take 45-60 minutes. I agreed because I didn't know how to cancel my order on the app and was also willing to wait longer. I called to check on our order at 6:50pm, 7:06pm, and 7:07pm - the employee kept diverting questions about the food preparation.  Finally, he said that our food would be ready in 20 to 30 more minutes. Although we did not receive any additional notifications, we decided to go to the restaurant to see if our food was ready. When we arrived at 7:20pm, we inquired about the status of our order. The waiter told us that it would take 10 more minutes. At this point, we asked to speak with the manager. However, the waiter repeatedly denied our requests, saying that the manager was "crazy" and that he wouldn't want to speak with us. He also told us that he couldn't give us a more specific time for our pickup since he wasn't in charge of cooking. When we asked for restaurant credit to make up for wasting our time, he said that this wasn't possible. After repeatedly asking, he finally offered us a soda. Throughout our conversation, the waiter told us multiple times that we could also try to cancel our order on GrubHub. However, we explained to him that we couldn't find the cancel option on GrubHub and that we were willing to wait just a few more minutes since the food was supposedly being prepared. This conversation probably lasted 5 minutes and the waiter was unclear about a final pickup time, so we finally told him that we expected our food to be ready in 8-10 more minutes.  After a few minutes of waiting outside, we saw the waiter come outside with a package. When we made eye contact with him, he curtly said, "Not for you!" with an attitude. After looking around on the sidewalk, he started to walk back to the restaurant. We tried to get his attention again, but he claimed that our food wasn't ready and that we could cancel our order. We asked him if he could check on our order with the manager or cooking staff. As he walked back into the restaurant, he looked at us and said, "I don't know how to talk to them. HMPH." I kid you not, he literally spitefully "hmph!"-ed at us!!  Based on the reactions of some people passing by, it was clear that his reaction and treatment toward us had been unprofessional, rude, and uncalled for. We felt so disrespected and humiliated by his treatment toward us that we decided to leave without our order. After 20 minutes, the restaurant called and hung up on me several times without saying anything.  After describing the situation to another friend, it occurred to us that the waiter might have been so unclear about our pickup time and so adamant about us cancelling our order because the restaurant had probably never started preparing our order in the first place. While I understand that it was Valentine's Day and that the place might have been busy and/or understaffed, if there was an issue, they should never have accepted my order in the first place. At the very least, they could have cancelled it from their end.  This was such an inconvenient and awful experience. For those who have had good experiences here, I am glad that you were able to enjoy your meals. However, I feel responsible for sharing my experience because I hope that no one else has to deal with this restaurant's ungracious customer service.

Delicious Thai food, generous portions, attentive staff - worth the wait. The server asked a couple to move a few minutes after they had been seated so our 4-top could fit and they graciously accommodated. I would definitely return, but not with more than one date.

I've been coming to this place a steady amount since it opened. I usually get a pick up order and pay with a credit card. Today I placed an order for pick up and was told it would be an hour and a half wait. When I arrived to pick up my food the server told me I had to pay in cash. While he was telling me this he was literally swiping a credit card for the guy in front of me in line. It was completely mind blowing. I didn't have cash, so I walked to my atm (with groceries in tow) and back. The guy still had an attitude about giving me my to-go order and was not apologetic at all about allowing some customers to pay with a card and not others. They can't keep up with the crowd and the food and service have seriously declined. There are tons of other mediocre Thai options in the city with wayyyy better service.
amazing food
So happy every time I come here. Every meal is exquisite. Even just walking by the restaurant and smelling the cooking is a culinary experience. Everyone who works here is lovely.

This place is small, but the food is amazing! I've been here multiple times since I've found it and it never fails. The staff has always been friendly and I've had no service issues ever. Try the shrimp Pad Thai. Oh and you can BYOB. If you forgot a bottle or want one, there's a place to get that across the street.

This place has some very wonderful Thai food. They are constantly running takeout orders in and out. Despite the food being very delicious, the restaurant is small and cramped. The chairs are uncomfortable. I would strongly recommend this place but it might be best to get take out.
So the food is really tasty, but the portions wasn't big. Ordered the seafood fry rice and didn't get enough seafood.

The food is pretty good, but the customer service is lacking and the portions are small for the cost.  I have ordered delivery from here and received high quality (albeit overpriced) thai fare (in  underwhelming portions) that was correctly made to order and adhered to dietary restrictions.  I’ve also had a friend walk into this restaurant to pick up only to have them wait an hour for it and receive something that was not prepared as requested, while they were subjected to racist comments from the cooks in the back. The friend in question also had multiple other people who walked in after them with larger and more complex orders served before them, and they called in for pick up in advance!  For me, that is a dealbreaker. I don’t do business with places that actively try to drive off their customers with inflammatory language, even when I am not the target of said affront.

I ordered from door dash and was let down. I ordered the Pad Thai and it came dry. I ordered the chicken but that was chewy and inedible and I ended up leaving it all to throw away. It probably got chewy while in transit because it was fried and the delivery took a while. I also ordered the massamun curry beef and wanted to add chicken so paid the extra $3. They said they can’t add chicken because the beef was already mixed in. Whatever, but didn’t refund me. When it arrived, there was one chunk of beef. 🙄 I don’t think I’ll be ordering from here again.
Great place

Secret gem in mount Vernon. BYOB and amazing Thai food. It’s a small place but worth the wait!! Love the eggplant appetizer, duck special and of course the pad Thai. Can’t go wrong with anything on the menu
Great food, excellent service with incredible price.
Restaurant was small and crowded, but the food was totally worth it!
Really good foods.I had vegetable Pad ke mao and I will go again for that. Modern and clean.
One of my favorite Thai place in Baltimore.
Love their ginger beef. Delicious. Also like that it's byob and the liquor store is across the street

PLEASE DO NOT EAT HERE. This is my second time dining. The first time was pleasant, the food was delicious, service okay, but with one server and a busy lunch crowd she was overwhelmed. The second time a gentleman who was 6’2 greeted me with an attitude. I started off with a Chicken Galangal Soup. I told him I would wait to order an entree after I finished my soup. Halfway through me soup he walked by and asked if I would order more food, I told him ,”No. I’m starting to get full.” Before I could say thank you he tells me to go and pay at the tablet. He did not offer me a check. He did not put down a check. There were two tables beside me and the restaurant went silent. He did not exercise proper restaurant etiquette and quite frankly embarrassed me. As I went up to pay I told him that he was wrong and that I felt embarrassed and I had been there before and was not treated that way. He told me it was ,”In my head.” And that I “made it up”. The two tables were still there and I asked them if I did anything wrong. The people still eating said he was completely rude. It was embarrassing and made them feel uncomfortable. I asked the server/manager for his name he told me that he would not give me his name and to never come back.  **UPDATE** I checked my bank account and was charged $58 dollars for the soup. Again. DO NOT EAT HERE.
This is a great place with amazing pad thai!!!
Great food and hospitality
Small and crowded.... but the food was amazing.

I'm giving 5 stars based on food and service. Great authentic thai food. It's not hard to find thai food in Baltimore but it is hard to find authentic thai food. Portions are perfect. You wouldnt think you were getting enough but actually as you eat you tend to realize that any more than what you got would have been too much. The only con is the size of the restaurant.  Way too small. You literally walk in and if you took about 7 steps then you are in the kitchen. Thats probably why there's only one waiter. If you had 2 they would be running into each other. No bathroom either. So hopefully you dont have to go. I recommend trying it on a non busy day/hour. We went on a Tuesday around 130p. So I think we lucked out.
Good fun, close and intimate space
I ordered this shrimp stew and rice... DISGUSTING! Shrimp is WAY overcooked. The delivery woman was rude. Didn’t even greet. First words out of her mouth was “where is tip?”
Delicious food, good service.

Some of the best Thai food in Baltimore. We are always happy with the Pad Z-Ew and any of their fried rice dishes. Seating is tight and the wait service might get busy during peak hours, but the food is always great.

Tried it the first time tonight and a little disappointed. Food were a little bland.  Ordered red curry and pad thai for me and the SO. I typically finish my meal in one seating but it didn't really taste good so maybe got to 1/3 of it and called it a day.  Off to find a better Thai restaurant
Just stopped by for a quick bite.  We had two really delicious currys.  Friendly, but really small place, mainly take out.

What a great authentic place to get Thai food. The ingredients are fresh and the small setting is perfect for an awesome date night or just an after work spot to stop in to. The staff was great and explained the menu so well to me. Loved the food start to finish!
Amazing experience with amazing service. The chicken basil is a wonder and has become my favorite place.
Fantastic hidden gem!
The dishes (Pad Z-Ew, etc) was way too salty.
Amazing beef massamun (seriously some of the best I’ve had and I am always searching out the best Thai food) with tender meat and amazing spice. Mango sticky rice was also delicious. Thanks so much!

After a long day of trying new things, like the Charm City Meadworks, it was time for dinner.  My sister found this place online and we decided to try it.  It is a small place, with few tables. We got in when it was pretty empty, but by the time we left it was filled.  Everything we got was good! I especially liked the wide noodles.
The best place to have Thai food. Both Drunken noodles and Fried rice were amazing.

I had to try this restaurant after learning about its close proximity to where I live and stellar patron reviews. The food there is delicious and very affordable. The last time I went I ordered a duck entrée and it was cooked to perfection. My friend who accompanied me liked this restaurant as well. I will definitely come here more often and try other entrees in addition to the duck dish!!
Small spot with a tight menu, done perfectly. Will definitely go again.
Yummy thai galangal soup and pad thai .

Good food and friendly service. Atmosphere feels a little cramped.  They've been open about a month now and still don't serve all the items listed on thier menu.  Update July 2018. Food is still good. They ended up abandoning the menu items I referenced, which was extremely disappointing. I only use this place for carry-out.
Had the salmon panang and the red curry sauce was great! Solid food, great atmosphere and a good location.
Thai "fine dining" with unremarkable food
(Translated by Google) Classic Thai cuisine  (Original) 經典的泰式料理
Great place to take someone to a date!

Very good food, reasonable prices. We got the papaya salad, the eggplant entree, and the pad z ew with tofu, and were pretty happy with everything. We thought the noodle dish could have used some more saucing. Service was good and attentive. Only four stars because even though we appreciate the no charge BYO option, I was pretty disappointed that the wine glasses were plastic tumblers. I felt it takes away a bit of the experience of enjoying the wine.
Always good. Love the pad-z-ew
Nice small Thai restaurant in Mount Vernon.
Awesome, little BYO spot with great, spicy Thai food.
Small, cute place on Charles Street. Lived a few blocks down from this restaurant and this was my go to Thai restaurant. Chicken pad thai was made to perfection
One of the better Thai places in Baltimore. I had the eggplant with tofu, asked for it spicy and it was delicious.
Absolutely delicious. Very authentic and well seasoned.

The best Thai food I've ever had in my life. The pad see ew uses a very fine noodle that I've never really seen before, and it makes the texture of the meal totally change. The pork belly and crispy shrimp rolls are also favorites!
Best Thai in town
The food has not failed to impress and has friendly staff. I'm currently a big fan of this establishment.

When it's good it's very very good, especially that chicken coconut soup... but when it's 'off', it's good but not fantastic. Part of the problem is that they are juggling too much in a tiny space- makes the front desk guy frazzled. Time to relocate to bigger digs guys!
Cozy. Good food.
Awesome food, great prices.
Excellent flavor, great atmosphere and incredible prices
Nice small place for simple Thai food.
Great Food
I am absolutely disappointed in the portion of mango and sticky rice. It was also very dry, undercooked and tasteless. For the money that I spent, I hoped my food would have at least been edible.

Great food. A nice variation on  the typical Thai menu of pad thai and drunken noodles. (But they have those, too) Very attentive service. Even though the restaurant is tiny (maybe 10 tables max), I was impressed that they still managed to accommodate most people as they came in. Small intimate size makes it perfect for a nice Thai meal on a cold winter day. They seem to have a thriving carryout and delivery business. I'll be back to try some other stuff on the menu!
Great food, excellent service and friendly atmosphere

Ordered Khun Nine with ubereats for delivery. We've eaten here before multiple times and loved the food, but tonight was a big disappointment. The crispy duck rolls were dry and chewy with minimal flavor that we had to find our own dipping sauce. The spicy eggplant had overcooked tofu and undercooked eggplant resulting in rubbery tofu and hard and crunchy eggplant. The pad kee mao was almost inedible. There was no flavor to it other than just spicy sauce, and we love spicy food. It was almost as if they forgot half the seasoning and just put in spicy sauce instead. Will not be ordering from here or going here again.
It’s a nice and students hangout place kind off .. Food is nice and have nice food ... I love it ...

Ordered tofu pad thai, extra spicy for dinner using UberEats. It. Was. Amazing. (and verrrrry spicy, just perfect!) This is the best thai restaurant in Baltimore. I need to go back for every meal. Why are you still reading this? GO!
Pretty good Thai food. Some dishes they make are a little different than you're used to but still really good.

It really is a hole in a wall with about 24 settings. But a very delicious hole indeed. We had the shrimp soup, chicken satay, chicken pad Thai but my children absolutely snuffed the duck pancakes. Super delicious, super quick to go in and out if they have seats available, and worth the wait.

My boyfriend’s favorite Thai place in downtown Baltimore! The place is cozy and it is most of the time packed if you go there during peak hours. Probably not a good place for big groups as the place is small. We usually order drunken noodles and pad thai but their curries are good too. Also order Thai iced tea! It’s a must!
best Thai place in Baltimore
Best Thai in Baltimore! Small intimate space, clever menu, and the chef is second to none.
Chicken Pad Thai was Scrumptious!  😀
Very small place , but delicious food in good area with good prices and bring your own booze
YUM
Delicious and spicy! The green curry left me wanting more! Also is byob!
Pretty good Thai food. With a nice atmosphere. Service was good as well as the spring rolls!
Go. Now. Stop deciding and go. This place is amazing.
The portions are generous. The food was first rate.
It may be small, but what it lacks in size, it fully makes up for in ambiance and flavor. Perfect for a date night or a quick bite at a very reasonable price. Do not pass this place up!
Nice, clean place, small but they have tables outside too. Very friendly people. The food was great I has khao soy and my wife who is Thai had the pad thai I would gladly return
Good food kinda pricy tho

Mediocre Thai food. I had pad see ew, which was served with angel hair style noodles, not the wide flat noodles I've had at many Thai places (including in Thailand). Barely any beef, very disappointed, especially after seeing the good reviews. My girlfriend got a noodle soup dish that was strangely bland.  I would not recommend this restaurant and will not visit again. It's a shame as we pass by there regularly.  The only reason they get a second star was for the young man that came after us to give us the crispy noodles that they forgot to give us for my girlfriend's soup.

This is not the place to dine in. Our server's English was very poor and she couldn' understand me. In fact, I had to repeat myself several times. They were very inattentive. Every single time I needed to ask for something or order anything, I had to flag them down, when we were one of two parties in the restaurant. When our server arrived with our entrees, she but didn't have the training/sense to clear away our appetizer plates, so we had to lift up our own plates and sit them aside. We ordered Jasmine rice (+$2) and it didn't show up with our meals. After eating for 10 minutes and then wondering where our rice was, I asked about her it and she brought only one out of the two (forgetting one). When she brought the second one, I said "I'm sorry but this isn't Jasmine," she said "Yes, it is," but I'm sure it wasn't. The portions were small and the vegetables were all over cooked. Another waiter came by and asked "Is everything okay?" And I said "Well, everything's okay, but..." and he just walked away -- I was mid-sentence. Clearly he wasn't even listening. At the end of the meal, I felt a strong need to tell him (I assume he was the manager) about my experience. When I told him about the jasmine rice matter and how it was NOT jasmine rice, he said "Oh, she doesn't speak English," as if that was a perfectly valid and acceptable thing. When I finished telling him everything, including the fact that he himself was rude, he just looked at me with an expressionless face, like he was a child being scolded-- and I was sooooo nice. His response was, "I'm sorry." No coupon. No free dessert. Nothing.  The only good of this place is that it's cheap. The food is very, very average.
Very good Thai food for lunch, never have had dinner here. My only wish was that it had a little more heat. It can be a little bit of a wait but just call ahead for pick up if you're in a rush.

The Thai iced tea was a little sweeter than I like but the pad thai was really good! The space is a little tight and there was only one, overworked server. However, our food came out pretty quickly. I'll definitely be going again!
Delicious food, affordable prices, byob. Has your standard Thai fare plus things I haven't seen other places. Great neighborhood spot
Great Thai food for a reasonable price!
Ordered delivery.  Each dish was better than the last. Spices were not overpowering and the not mild dishes had robust flavor.

Horrible.. ordered for delivery and called after an hour. They got upset that I questioned the food that would have picked up be hot if they delivered .  They canceled my order because I demanded the delivery food be hot and fresh.  Terrible Customer service which sucks because I heard the food is good. Not worth the frustration.
Their massaman blows my mind every time I've had it. I haven't had a single dish I haven't loved and I've tried at least ten entrees.
Amazing spring rolls. Very friendly staff!  Gotta try the thai ice tea
Solid Thai food
Good food.  Great price.   BYOB
I've eaten there 3 times this week. The basil chicken is awesome. Probably going to get it for dinner tonight...
I've been going to this place since they first open. Today is my fourth time. Love the food. Lunch special deals are very affordable. I would go back again next week to try a different dish.
Online it says they open at 4:30, arrived at 4:40 to a hand written note on the door saying "break time, be back at 5pm". Showed back up at 5:20, still closed. Disappointed.
Very intimate setting with amazing food and good portions.
. Dining room provides casual dining atmosphere.  The price is right for most dishes and locate in the middle of the Baltimore Metro Area.  Huge portion and very nice people working there. A+++
